rg/wiki/Integers_modulo_n" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Integers modulo n=
">integers modulo <i>N</i></a> and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Product_of_rings" title=3D"Product of rings">direct product</a> of the=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring_of_integers" title=3D"Ring o=
f integers">rings of integers</a> modulo the <i>n</i><sub><i>i</i></sub>. T=
his means that for doing a sequence of arithmetic operations in <span class=
=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathm=
l-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http=
://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \mathbb {Z} /N\ma=
thbb {Z} ,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
