-align: -0.838ex; width:6.458ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ma=
thbb {Z} /n_{i}\mathbb {Z} }"></span> and then get the result by applying t=
he isomorphism (from the right to the left). This may be much faster than t=
he direct computation if <i>N</i> and the number of operations are large. T=
his is widely used, under the name <i>multi-modular computation</i>, for <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_algebra" title=3D"Linear alge=
bra">linear algebra</a> over the integers or the <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Rational_number" title=3D"Rational number">rational numbers<=
/a>.
</p><p>The theorem can also be restated in the language of <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorics" title=3D"Combinatorics">combinatori=
cs</a> as the fact that the infinite <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Arithmetic_progression" title=3D"Arithmetic progression">arithmetic prog=
ressions</a> of integers form a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/He=
lly_family" title=3D"Helly family">Helly family</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_remai=
nder_theorem#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Proof">Proof</h2><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DChinese_remainder_theorem&=
amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Proof"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The existence and the uniqueness of the solution may be proven independe=
ntly. However, the first proof of existence, given below, uses this uniquen=
ess.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Uniqueness">Uniqueness</h3>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DChinese_remainde=
r_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Uniquen=
ess"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>Suppose that <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x=
</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</sp=
an> are both solutions to all the congruences. As <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> give the same remainder, when divided=
 by <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n<sub>i</sub></i></span>, their difference <=
span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =E2=88=92 <i>y</i></span> is a multiple of =
each <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n<sub>i</sub></i></span>. As the <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml"><i>n<sub>i</sub></i></span> are pairwise coprime, their produ=
ct <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>N</i></span> also divides <span class=3D"texh=
tml"><i>x</i> =E2=88=92 <i>y</i></span>, and thus <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> are congruent modulo <span class=3D"t=
exhtml"><i>N</i></span>. If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-styl=
e:italic;">x</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:it=
alic;">y</span>  are supposed to be non-negative and less than <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>N</i></span> (as in the first statement of the theorem), th=
en their difference may be a multiple of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>N</i></=
span> only if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D <i>y</i></span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Existence_(first_proof)"><s=
pan id=3D"Existence_.28first_proof.29"></span>Existence (first proof)</h3><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</spa=
n><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DChinese_remainder=
_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Existenc=
e (first proof)"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket=
">]</span></span></div>
<p>The map
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
