bmod {N}}\mapsto (x{\bmod {n}}_{1},\ldots ,x{\bmod {n}}_{k})}"></span></dd>=
</dl>
<p>maps <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congruence_class" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Congruence class">congruence classes</a> modulo <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml"><i>N</i></span> to sequences of congruence classes modu=
lo <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n<sub>i</sub></i></span>. The proof of unique=
ness shows that this map is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inject=
ive" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Injective">injective</a>. As the <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain_of_a_function" title=3D"Domain of=
 a function">domain</a> and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co=
domain" title=3D"Codomain">codomain</a> of this map have the same number of=
 elements, the map is also <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surject=
ive" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Surjective">surjective</a>, which prove=
s the existence of the solution.
</p><p>This proof is very simple but does not provide any direct way for co=
mputing a solution. Moreover, it cannot be generalized to other situations =
where the following proof can.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Existence_(constructive_pro=
of)"><span id=3D"Existence_.28constructive_proof.29"></span>Existence (cons=
tructive proof)</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DChinese_remainder_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"E=
dit section: Existence (constructive proof)"><span>edit</span></a><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Existence may be established by an explicit construction of <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-16" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_r=
emainder_theorem#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This construction may be split i=
nto two steps, first solving the problem in the case of two moduli, and the=
n extending this solution to the general case by <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_induction" title=3D"Mathematical induction">ind=
uction</a> on the number of moduli.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Case_of_two_moduli">Case of=
 two moduli</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Chinese_remainder_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit =
section: Case of two moduli"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsec=
tion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>We want to solve the system:
</p>
