(also called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ideal_(ring_theory)#T=
ypes_of_ideals" title=3D"Ideal (ring theory)">comaximal ideals</a>). Two <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ideal_(ring_theory)" title=3D"Ideal =
(ring theory)">ideals</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">I</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">J</span> are coprime if there are elements <span class=3D"mwe-math-ele=
ment mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-mat=
h-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/19=
98/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle i\in I}">
